column5: Wall, I warned ya..         Some nice garbage on Unwin rd..   Hey look a Unicycle   That's it.
Thanks Paul !  ...and that ain't a unicycle! LOL...got two wheels bud!

Well those pics wern't boring,they were quite nice except for like you said,ALL THE GARBAGE ITS EVERYWHERE   , people just dont care they think the world is their personal garbage dump  ...its to bad..thanks for sharing...cheers
lol even if you put "boring" up i'm sure alot of people would come in for the "Pictures"  we love pictures right? Thanks for the pics
The amount of garbage is horrible.
maybe its a unicycle with a training wheel

It's a penny farthing, reportedly the first true bicycle that could produce decent speed.  They were popular in the last half of the 19th century.  Don't hit a pothole or you're going over the handlebars.
Nice pics Paul!  They weren't that boring...seeing water always makes me think "Hmmm...wonder where the fish are in there"....LOL.
Nice pics nothing wrong with them keep'em comming.

I live 5 minutes from there! Not surprised by the garbage at all! No excuses, but if you consider the number of people who use that area, travel past or through it, then add the winter months and the city's in-ability to clean during the snowy months, I'm not at all surpirsed by that! As I said, no excuses. HH
